The paper deals with complexity results related to the H-index, which is a measure of scientific productivity and impact. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), cybernetics (cs.CY), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Among these, cs.DS and cs.IR seem to be the most likely categories, as they deal with algorithms and data structures for efficient information retrieval and manipulation, which are relevant to the H-index manipulation problem addressed in the paper.
